{{infobox country at games | NOC = EGY | NOCname = [[Egyptian Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1972 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.egyptianolympic.org }}&nbsp;{{ar icon}} {{en icon}} | location = [[Munich]] | competitors = 23 (men) | sports = 5 | flagbearer = [[Kamal Kamel Mohammed]] (Basketball) | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = [[Egypt at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games }}
'''[[Egypt]]''' competed at the '''[[1972 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Munich]], [[West Germany]]. The North African nation made its Olympic debut in 1912.
The Egyptian contingent included 28 male athletes, 1 female athlete and 18 officials. Because of the [[Munich massacre]], some members of the Egyptians contingent left the Olympics early.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20120808032119/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1972/1972s1.pdf</ref>
