{{Distinguish|Lirim Kastrati}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Lirim Kastrati |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Lirim Kastrati |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|1|16|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Kamenica, Kosovo|Kamenica]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|FR Yugoslavia]] |height = {{convert|1.65|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] |currentclub = [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]] |clubnumber = 22 |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2014 |youthclubs1 = [[:sq:KF Kika|Kika]] |youthyears2 = 2014–2017 |youthclubs2 = [[Shkëndija Tiranë]] |youthyears3 = 2017–2018 |youthclubs3 = [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]] |years1 = 2017– |clubs1 = [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]] |caps1 = 24 |goals1 = 10 |nationalyears1 = 2017– |nationalteam1 = [[Kosovo national under-19 football team|Kosovo U19]] |nationalcaps1 = 4 |nationalgoals1 = 0<!--Only matches as FIFA member are included.--> |nationalyears2 = 2017– |nationalteam2 = [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] |nationalcaps2 = 1 |nationalgoals2 = 0<!--Only matches as FIFA member are included.--> |nationalyears3 = 2018– |nationalteam3 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps3 = 1 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |club-update = 22 October 2018 |nationalteam-update = 11 October 2018 }} '''Lirim Kastrati''' (born 16 January 1999) is a Kosovar professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Croatian club [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]] and the [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo national team]].
==Club career== ===Lokomotiva=== On 17 February 2018, Kastrati made his debut as professional footballer in a 1–0 away defeat against [[NK Istra 1961|Istra 1961]] after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nklokomotiva.hr/vijest/istra-1961-lokomotiva-1-0-663|title=Istra 1961 - Lokomotiva 1:0|language=Croatian|publisher=[[NK Lokomotiva]]|date=17 February 2018}}</ref> On 10 March 2018, he scored his first two goals in a 4–1 away win against [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nklokomotiva.hr/vijest/velika-pobjeda-u-gradskom-derbiju-dinamo-lokomotiva-1-4-679|title=VELIKA POBJEDA U GRADSKOM DERBIJU! Dinamo - Lokomotiva 1:4|trans-title=GREAT WINNER IN CITY DERBY! Dinamo - Lokomotiva 1:4|language=Croatian|publisher=[[NK Lokomotiva]]|date=10 March 2018}}</ref> On 16 September 2018, Kastrati scored the first [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] of his career in a 2–5 away win over [[NK Slaven Belupo|Slaven Belupo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.germanijak.hr/vijesti/spektakl-u-koprivnici-sedam-golova-hattrick-mladog-reprezentativca-kosova/51468|title=Spektakl u Koprivnici - sedam golova, hat-trick mladog reprezentativca Kosova|trans-title=Spectacle in Koprivnica - seven goals, hat-trick of a young Kosovo player|language=Croatian|website=Germanijak|date=16 September 2018}}</ref>
==International career== ===Youth=== ====Under-19==== On 1 October 2017, Kastrati was named as part of the [[Kosovo national under-19 football team|Kosovo U19]] squad for [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification#Group 6|2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualifications]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=22655|title=Kombëtarja U19 udhëtoi për në Austri|trans-title=National U19 team traveled to Austria|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=1 October 2017}}</ref> On 3 October 2017, he made his debut with Kosovo U19 in a match against [[Austria national under-19 football team|Austria U19]] after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=22766|title=Humbje minimale e Kombëtares U-19 përballë Austrisë|trans-title=Minimal defeat of national U19 team against Austria|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=3 October 2017}}</ref>
====Under-21==== On 6 November 2017, Kastrati received a call-up from [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo U21]] for [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 5|2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] matches against [[Israel national under-21 football team|Israel U21]] and [[Azerbaijan national under-21 football team|Azerbaijan U21]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=24057|title=Prekazi publikoi listën e futbollistëve për ndeshjet me Izraelin dhe Azerbejxhanin|trans-title=Prekazi published the list of footballers for matches with Israel and Azerbaijan|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=6 November 2017}}</ref> On 14 November 2017, he made his debut with Kosovo U21 in a match against Azerbaijan U21 after coming on as a substitute at 46th minute in place of [[Mirlind Daku]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/?p=24543|title=Kombëtarja U21 barazoi me Azerbejxhanin në Baku|trans-title=National U21 team draw with Azerbaijan in Baku|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=14 November 2017}}</ref>
===Senior=== On 5 October 2018, Kastrati received a call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] for the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League D#Group 3|2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Malta national football team|Malta]] and [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/2018/10/05/challandes-publikon-listen-e-futbollisteve/|title=Challandes publikon listën e futbollistëve|trans-title=Challandes publish the list of footballers|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=5 October 2018}}</ref> On 11 October 2018, he made his debut with Kosovo in a match against Malta after coming on as a substitute at 83rd minute in place of [[Vedat Muriqi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/federata/2018/10/11/kosova-feston-edhe-kunder-maltes-dardanet-te-paret-ne-grupin-3/|title=Kosova feston edhe kundër Maltës, "Dardanët" të parët në Grupin 3|trans-title=Kosovo celebrates even against Malta, "Dardanians" first in Group 3|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=11 October 2018}}</ref>
