{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Pakistan Sailing Federation |abbrev = PSAF |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Sailing (sport)|Sailing]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|1969}} |aff = [[International Sailing Federation]] |affdate = |region = [[Asian Sailing Federation]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Karachi]] |location = National Sailing Centre |president = K G Hussain SI(M) |secretary = CDR M Akram Tariq |url = |countryflag = Pakistan |more = }} The '''Pakistan Sailing Federation''' is the national [[Sports governing body|governing body]] of the sport of [[Sailing (sport)|Sailing]] in [[Pakistan]].
After [[Pakistan Movement|Independence]], sailing activities were undertaken by the Karachi Yacht Club. In 1969, the Pakistan Yachting Association (PYA) was formed. The name of PYA was changed to Pakistan Sailing Federation in 1996.
The Federation is affiliated with
* [[International Sailing Federation]]<ref>http://www.sailing.org/about/members/mnas/pakistan.php</ref> * Asian Sailing Federation <ref>{{cite web |url=http://asiansailing.org/mna_pak.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714181219/http://asiansailing.org/mna_pak.php |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref> * [[Pakistan Sports Board]] * [[Pakistan Olympic Association]]
