{{Infobox football biography | name = Steve Bizasène | image = | image_size = | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|04|24}} | birth_place = [[Pointe-à-Pitre]], [[Guadeloupe]] | height = 1.72 m | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1991–1998 | clubs1 = [[AS Beauvais]] | caps1 = 115 | goals1 = 7 | years2 = 1998–2002 | clubs2 = [[ES Wasquehal]] | caps2 = 129 | goals2 = 7 | years3 = 2002–2007 | clubs3 = [[US Lesquin]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | nationalyears1 = 2006–2008 | nationalteam1 = [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] | nationalcaps1 = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | manageryears1 = –2012 | managerclubs1 = [[Guadeloupe under-20 national football team|Guadeloupe U-20]] | manageryears2 = 2012– | managerclubs2 = [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] | manageryears3 = | managerclubs3 = | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
'''Steve Bizasène''' (born 24 April 1970 in [[Pointe-à-Pitre]]) is a [[Guadeloupe]]an professional [[association footballer|football player]] and [[association football manager|manager]].
In 1991, he began his career for the [[AS Beauvais]]. In Summer 1998 he transferred to the [[ES Wasquehal]]. In July 2002 he moved to [[US Lesquin]].
In 2006, he made his debut for the [[Guadeloupe national football team]].
Since September 2012 he is a head coach of the [[Guadeloupe national football team]].<ref name="NFT">{{NFT player|id=9374|accessdate=}}</ref>
